                en: "Riserva or artisanal dried pasta uses slow drying methods at low temperatures (below 40°C) over 24-48 hours or even longer, compared to industrial pasta dried at high temperatures (80-100°C) in 2-3 hours. Slow drying preserves wheat proteins and flavors, creates a rougher texture that holds sauce better, and produces pasta that maintains better structure when cooked. Bronze die extrusion (trafilatura al bronzo) often accompanies this method, creating a porous surface. Premium brands like Rustichella d'Abruzzo, Benedetto Cavalieri, and Martelli use these traditional methods, resulting in pasta with superior taste, texture, and cooking performance.",
