            en: "Egg yolks in fresh pasta provide multiple functions beyond structural binding. Lecithin (phosphatidylcholine) is a powerful natural emulsifier that helps integrate water and fat components, creating smoother dough and better sauce adhesion. Lysozyme, an enzyme naturally present in egg whites, has antimicrobial properties that inhibit bacterial growth, extending the shelf life of fresh pasta (though still limited to 2-3 days refrigerated). Eggs also contribute proteins that strengthen the pasta network and provide the characteristic yellow color from carotenoids.",
